title: Phillipsburg boys soccer team shuts out Bridgewater in rain (PHOTOS)
text:
Complete Box Score » 
Phillipsburg High School’s boys soccer team scored three second-half goals to surge past Bridgewater 3-0 in the rain on Tuesday afternoon at the Phillipsburg Athletic Complex. 
Alec Coleman had a goal and an assist for the Stateliners. Noah Long and Tyler Mitchell also scored. 
Bernie Caffrey (six saves) and Quinn Fortner (four saves) helped P’burg to the shutout. 
Scroll through the gallery atop this post for photos from the soggy game.
